ms he is credited with producing, Motoki also had an influence on other Kurosawa films.  For example, he was involved in the production of Rashomon.  Motoki sent the letter to screenwriter Shinobu Hashimoto inviting him to help expand the script of Rashomon.During the late 1940s, Motoki joined with directors Kurosawa, Senkichi Taniguchi and Kajiro Yamamoto (eventually joined by Naruse as well) to form a short-lived independent production company, the Motion Picture Art Association, which was responsible for such films as Rashomon, The Quiet Duel and Stray Dog.", "biography_author": "Wikidata", "date_of_biography": "2022-05-19T13:04:51.189717+10:00", "external_links": [{"id": 3098, "uri": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/S%C5%8Djir%C5%8D_Motoki"}], "uuid": "417b29db-a1a7-4474-b48a-8dbf70a89067", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "28782", "external_references": [{"id": 13143, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q11520413"}, {"id": 13144, "source": {"name": "VIAF", "slug": "viaf"}, "source_identifier": "68202972"}, {"id": 13145, "source": {"name": "LOC Auth", "slug": "loc-auth"}, "source_identifier": "n96106013"}, {"id": 13146, "source": {"name": "WorldCat", "slug": "worldcat"}, "source_identifier": "lccn-n96106013"}], "date_modified": "2023-09-13T12:32:43.588422+10:00"}, {"id": 22350, "name": "Toho Kabushiki Kaisha", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 2166358, "title": "Kagemusha", "work_id": 80857, "role": "production company", "role_id": 941, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 924481, "title": "Metropolis", "work_id": 93799, "role": "production company", "role_id": 941, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 1996073, "title": "Tokyo Olympiad [Widescreen]", "work_id": 92474, "role": "production company", "role_id": 941, "is_primary": true}, {"id": 2166617, "title": "Kakushi Toride No San Akunin = The Hidden Fortress (Cinemascope Print)", "work_id": 115706, "role": "production company", "role_id": 941, "is_primary": true}, {"